    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A colorless, sweet-smelling, sweet-tasting, non-flammable, slightly water-soluble gas, N2O. It is used chiefly as an anesthetic in dentistry and surgery, and in the manufacture of chemicals, such as aerosols.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046682/Random House Dictionary of the English Language (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gas incoloro, de olor dulce, de sabor dulce, no inflamable y levemente soluble en agua, fórmula N2O. Es utilizado fundamentalmente como anestésico en odontología y cirugía, y en la fabricación de productos químicos, como por ejemplo aerosoles.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een kleurloos, zoetgeurig, zoet smakend, onbrandbaar, lichtelijk in water oplossend gas, N2O. Het wordt vooral gebruikt als narcoticum in tandheelkunde en chirurgie, en bij de fabricage van chemicaliën zoals aerosols.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052381/Van Dale Engels-Nederlands (1989)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>一種無色、味道宜人、帶甜味、不可燃、微溶於水的氣體，化學式為N2O。 主要做為牙科和手術的麻醉劑，也可用來製造氣溶膠等的化學物質。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
